        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 3:26AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 325 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Silver Lake State Park, or 13 miles west of Hart,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail and 30 mph winds.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hart...                Shelby...              Mears...
Silver Lake SP...      Elbridge...            Walkerville...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
